cs.DC, cs.IR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on comparing two edge computing platforms, which involves distributed computing and parallel processing. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions a suite of performance metrics used to evaluate the edge platforms, which could involve information retrieval techniques. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Edge computing involves processing data at the edge of the network, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses platform features available to developers and current issues and challenges in deploying the platforms, which are related to software engineering. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper evaluates the performance of the edge platforms and compares them to cloud-only implementations, which could involve systems and control techniques.
